The paper discusses the use of Deep Learning for semantic segmentation of remote sensing images, which is a popular topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also discusses the use of various 2D and 3D architectures for processing the data, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also deals with the processing of spatial and spectral dimensions of the data, which is related to graphics (cs.GR) and information retrieval (cs.IR).
